          "text": "philosophy and gymnastics; For I do not think that it is good for rulers to have great affections of rulers, nor strong friendship and fellowship, which does not even kiss each other and everything that love affects. and by this work even the cruel tyrants learned; for Aristogeiton's love and the friendship of Armodius, a certain fact, overthrew their principle. so that he was put in shame",
