          "text": "Be pleased, lovers, by the malice of those who are set, those who rule with advantage, but those who rule with valor; but to whom it was simply thought good, because of the rest of the souls. But many of these good things are not legislated, and as I said, you cannot understand them. Remembering that it is said better to be openly a thief, and indeed of the brave and excellent, even the ignoble of others, and that therefore the prayer to the beloved is above all admirable, no matter how beautiful he is, and what he does well is",
