          "text": "I mean, if you call someone, look at Socrates, O Agathon, about whom I, a peasant, praise; but I have seen that the wise men of the earth are happy, whether you take care of them or of many; but not these we; for we also went there and were among the many; But if other wise men are happy, then if I do not care about them, what is it, perhaps, that they are ugly, or what do you say? You're right, it seems. But the many are not ugly or what kind of ugly?",
