          "text": "But this one fills our alienation without emptiness, but with intimacy, those gatherings with others of all kinds, in feasts, in dances, in sacrifices, becoming of the day; prudence without a porizon, ferocity without limits; generous with favor, ungifted with disfavor; see wise, gracious gods; zealous of fortune, possessor of fortune; father of Tryphus, Abrotetus, Chlidus, Charitas, Himerus, Pothus; diligent in good, negligent in evil; in pain, in fear, in desire, in",
