          "text": "But an adverb, it seems Phaedron, but love. after this, he did not see Socrates clothed in a long time. And do not, my friend Agathon, praise me for the teaching of the word, saying that first of all you should fear him. Show me who Eros is, and then his works, this principle I love. Tell me, then, about Love, because you have become what you are, well and majestically, and",
